<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="1073" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1073">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-19T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1915, 6 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1231. Your 1096, September 29, forwarded to Paris, October 4. French
                            Ambassador here now inquires what further action this Government
                            proposes to take. Your efforts and protest of Consul General at Beirut
                            are approved. Cable whether examination of French archives has been
                            continued.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>